&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place item at the curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Residents of apartments/condos should take electronics to their building&amp;rsquo;s designated drop-off area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If item is soiled with food/beverage, place it in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this empty, unsoiled item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be placed in the Garbage Bin, Blue Bin, Green Bin or put down the drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For more information and locations check&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.productcare.org/products/hhw/ontario/&quot;&gt;https://www.productcare.org/products/hhw/ontario/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This type of waste is not accepted by the City of Toronto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do not place this item in the Garbage Bin, Green Bin or Blue Bin, and do not bring this item to the City&#x27;s Drop-Off Depots or Community Environment Days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make arrangements with a private company specializing in handling this type of waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;These metal items are collected at your curbside on your scheduled Garbage Bin collection day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break down, bundle and/or tie if applicable before setting the item out for pick up 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Containers with hazardous products must be disposed of as Household Hazardous Waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any black plastic in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty, rinsed item, with lid on, in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Empty and rinse (if necessary and possible) this item before placing it in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is not collected at curbside.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If less than 1.2 meters (4 feet) in length, item can be taken to one of the City&#x27;s Drop-Off Depots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If longer than 1.2 meters (4 feet), make arrangements with private company specializing in disposing of this type of waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please tie into rolls measuring no longer than 1.2 metres (4 ft) and weighing less than 20 kilograms (44 lbs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item at the curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove and discard any foil or plastic seals in the Garbage Bin, then rinse before placing in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;books that are in good condition&amp;nbsp;or bringing to a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Day&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please place large metal household appliance right at your curbside on your scheduled Garbage Bin collection day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For safety reasons, please remove doors from fridges, freezers, ovens and other large appliances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please set out appliance and door(s) for pick up 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Items can also be dropped off for reuse at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;City of Toronto residents can drop off up to 10 passenger and light truck tires per day free of charge at some&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Only passenger and light truck tires will be accepted. All other tire types (e.g., heavy truck, forklift and large off-road tires) will not be accepted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check the &lt;a href=&quot;https://rpra.ca/programs/tires/collectionsites/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Resource Productivity &amp;amp; Recovery Authority&lt;/a&gt; for other tire collection sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; ensuring the lid closes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If container is not empty, check if the contents are &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt; and dispose of properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any black and/or compostable plastic in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty, rinsed item, with lid, pump or sprayer on, in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be placed in the Garbage Bin, Blue Bin, Green Bin or put down the drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively,&amp;nbsp;place item 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin on your scheduled garbage collection day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take apart large heavy items to make collection manageable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any black and/or compostable plastic in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty and clean item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Batteries are&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be disposed of in the garbage, Blue Bin (recycling) or Green Bin (organics).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For safe storage, place used batteries back in their original packaging or cover the positive terminal with clear packing tape, duct tape or electrical tape or place in a clear plastic bag (wrap multiple batteries together).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take batteries&amp;nbsp;to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;. For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&amp;nbsp;In an apartment or condo building, pickup needs to be arranged by building staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Items can also be dropped off for reuse at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;G&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;arbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Take this item to a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depot&lt;/a&gt;. Disposal fees may apply.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empty and rinse this item before placing it in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place the items inside two plastic bags (double-bagged) and place them in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paper with excessive paint or glue should go in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place pumpkins and jack-o-lanterns in your &lt;strong&gt;Yard Waste&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Yard waste in plastic bags will not be collected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use kraft paper bags from October to March as items may freeze to containers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you do not have other Yard Waste, cut pumpkin in quarters and put in your Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Place this empty item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Any type of black or compostable plastic is not accepted and should be placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If possible, please remove handle from shovel blade.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please set out the shovel for pick up 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; on your scheduled &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; collection day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt; and MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin or Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt; Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in your Yard Waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Yard waste in plastic bags will not be collected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use kraft paper bags from October to March as items may freeze to containers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leave your grass clippings on your lawn; yard waste containing grass clippings or sod will not be collected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please place poisonous and invasive plants in your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, please&amp;nbsp;wrap item with cardboard, thick paper, fabric or bubble wrap to prevent breakage during collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Then label it &quot;glass item&quot; and place it 0.5 metres (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin on your scheduled garbage collection day. If you live in a multi-residential building, please&amp;nbsp;take this item to your building&amp;rsquo;s designated area for oversized items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All wood waste, including that which is suffering from the emerald ash borer beetle, can be put to the curb as long as it does not exceed 7.5 cm (3 inches) in diameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Securely tie hedge trimmings, brush or branches. Bundles can be up to 1.2 m (4ft.) in length and 0.6 m (2ft.) in width, weighing less than 20 kgs/44lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If items exceed 7.5 cm (3 inches) in diameter, please make arrangements with a private company specializing in handling this type of waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is not collected curbside.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depot&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;Please note disposal fees may apply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Never pour down the sink, drain or toilet because it can cause sewer backups&amp;nbsp;in your home and neighbourhood.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For amounts between 10 and 50 litres/kilograms (no more than 20 litres per container), you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311.&amp;nbsp;In an apartment or condo building, pickup needs to be arranged by building staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please remove the sand, then place the pool filter 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; on your scheduled garbage collection day for free pick-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bag tags are not required for oversize items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Green Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrap sharp edges with thick or multi-layered material (e.g. paper, cardboard, soft plastic, fabric) before placing in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Broken glass from items that are accepted in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g. jars, bottles) can be placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt; and MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin, Green Bin or put down the drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt; Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The City does not accept this item in its Blue Bin Recycling or Green Bin Organics programs, even if it is labelled &amp;ldquo;recyclable&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;compostable&amp;rdquo; or &quot;biodegradable&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin, Green Bin or put down the drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/li&gt;
