&lt;li&gt;Fluorescent light bulbs and tubes contain mercury and are&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW).&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HHW MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin or Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt; Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Remove and discard any ribbons, ropes and grommets and place the paper bag/box in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Metallic/foil wrapping paper goes in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is not collected at the curbside and is not accepted at City of Toronto Drop-Off Depots or Community Environment Days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider donating or selling this item.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;Alternatively, please make arrangements with a private company to dispose of this item.&lt;/li&gt;
