&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you find an injured or dead animal, please contact &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;311&lt;/a&gt;. If found dead on private property, skunks, raccoons, opossums and unowned domestic animals need to be bagged and placed at the curb for pickup, but coyotes and deer do not need to be.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can also make an appointment to bring dead animals to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/community-people/animals-pets/animal-shelters/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Toronto Animal Shelter&lt;/a&gt; for disposal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the dead animal is under a deck or porch, please call a private company for animal removal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Separate paper/cardboard (if applicable) from rigid plastic packaging and place each separately in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any plastic/foil liners or windows and place those in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flatten box and place in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in your&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Green Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Line either your indoor container or outdoor Green Bin with a plastic bag or kraft paper bag. Do not line both.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Place hard, non-black, plastic pails and drums in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Remove any metal handles and place those in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Items can also be dropped off for reuse at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discard any plastic lids in your &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;, then empty and rinse (if necessary and possible) this item before placing it in your &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any foam that is soiled, shorter than 4&quot; or black in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place empty item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt; (recycling). Stained foam is fine, but it must be free of residue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place crinkly/non-stretchy, black and compostable bags in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If paper is lined with wax or plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), then place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this empty item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Items can also be dropped off for reuse at &lt;a style=&quot;background-color: #ffffff; font-family: &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot; href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt; Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item at your curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Separate toilet tank and bowl unless it&#x27;s a one-piece toilet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If applicable and possible, please remove any seats that are not ceramic/porcelain and place those in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

