&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider returning the licence plate to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ontario.ca/page/services&quot;&gt;Service Ontario&lt;/a&gt; location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;object id=&quot;__symantecPKIClientMessenger&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot; data-install-updates-user-configuration=&quot;true&quot; data-extension-version=&quot;0.4.0.129&quot;&gt;&lt;/object&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dispose excess cannabis and plants as Yard Waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place in Garbage Bin when Yard Waste collection is not available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Never pour down the sink, drain or toilet because it can cause sewer backups in your home and neighbourhood.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Either leave it to harden or saturate with a paper towel and then place in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item, regardless of the material (e.g. corrugated plastic, plastic sleeve, paperboard) in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wooden stakes should also be placed in the Garbage Bin. Metal supports can be taken to certain City &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; as scrap metal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Election signs are accepted for recycling at certain &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot;&gt;City Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; for a limited time following an election.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place disc and any plastic parts in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place empty paper case in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place boxes without any plastic or foil layer in the Blue Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place boxes with a plastic or foil layer (can be revealed by ripping slowly) in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place COVID-19 rapid at-home test kit materials (e.g. swab, solution tube, test device) in the garbage bagged.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place paper (e.g. instructions, box) in the Blue Bin (recycling).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Businesses must make arrangements with a private company to dispose of this item. Some are listed on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ontario.ca/page/safe-handling-and-management-rapid-antigen-covid-19-testing-waste&quot;&gt;https://www.ontario.ca/page/safe-handling-and-management-rapid-antigen-covid-19-testing-waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items or bringing to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Day&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metal pots/pans can be brought to certain &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; as scrap metal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completely submerge flares in water and soak them overnight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrap soaked flares in a plastic bag (to keep them from drying out) and dispose in the &lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dispose of flares in small quantities (up to 10 items).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This type of waste is not accepted by the City of Toronto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do not place this item in the garbage, recycling (Blue Bin), organics (Green Bin) and do not bring this item to the City&#x27;s Drop-Off Depots. It will not be accepted as Household Hazardous Waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring this item to the Canadian Power and Sail Squadrons (CPS-ECP) &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cps-ecp.ca/events/safety-equipment-flare-disposal-days-2/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Safety Equipment and Flare Disposal Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items or bringing to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Day&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, remove and dispose of ironing board cover in the garbage and place board out as an oversized item on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider keeping this item for reuse or donating this item.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;. If possible, remove metal pieces and place those in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove as much paint as possbile (a thin, dry layer is fine), then place non-black plastic trays/liners in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place black plastic trays/liners&amp;nbsp;in the Garbage Bin after as much paint as possbile is removed (i.e. either used up or disposed of as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any black foam and pieces shorter than 4&quot; in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider keeping this item for reuse or donating this item.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bags that still have paint (more than a thin layer) must be disposed of as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; or keeping this item for reuse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;. If possible, remove metal pieces and place those in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any plastic covers/sheets in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The City does not accept this item in its Blue Bin Recycling or Green Bin Organics programs, even if it is labelled recyclable, compostable or biodegradable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep this item for reuse or place it in the &lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Containers with paint (more than a thin, dry layer) must be disposed of as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove as much paint as possible (a thin, dry layer is fine), then place non-black plastic containers and lids in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place black plastic paint containers and lids in the garbage after as much paint as possible is removed (i.e. either used up or disposed of as Household Hazardous Waste).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any item made of PVC in the &lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place bubbled/padded, crinkly/non-stretchy, black and compostable bags in the Garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove as much tape and labels as possible and put those in the Garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place empty bags that are at least somewhat soft and stretchy in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin (recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items&amp;nbsp;or bringing to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Day&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; after removing any batteries and disposing of them as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart watches should be disposed of as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/electronic-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Electronic Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This type of waste is not accepted by the City of Toronto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do not place this item in the garbage, recycling (Blue Bin), organics (Green Bin) and do not bring this item to the City&#x27;s Drop-Off Depots. It will not be accepted as Household Hazardous Waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact the manufacturer for information on proper disposal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact a veterinary clinic or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/community-people/animals-pets/animal-shelters/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Toronto Animal Shelters&lt;/a&gt; (416-338-PAWS) to discuss disposal options.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Do not touch the dead animal with your bare hands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Wear gloves or use a plastic bag to pick it up and put inside two plastic bags (double bag). Then tie the bags closed and place in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;If you find the dead squirrel on City property (e.g. road, sidewalk, park) please contact &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;311&lt;/a&gt; or double bag it and place it in the &lt;strong&gt;garbage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place clean item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place all black and compostable plastic in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The City does not accept coffee pods in its Blue Bin Recycling or Green Bin Organics programs, even if they are labelled &amp;ldquo;recyclable&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;compostable&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coffee pods can be returned to retailers/manufacturers that have take-back programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove all decorations before placing this item out as &lt;strong&gt;Yard Waste.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in a kraft paper yard waste bag, yard waste bin, or any open top, rigid reusable container with handles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item may be taken to a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depot&lt;/a&gt; when Yard Waste collection is not available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;_GoBack&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break apart cardboard box and place in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place inner foil bag with lid in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; bagged.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place item at the curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Residents of apartments/condos should take electronics to their building&amp;rsquo;s designated drop-off area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The City does not accept this item in its Blue Bin Recycling or Green Bin Organics programs, even if it is labelled &amp;ldquo;recyclable&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;compostable&amp;rdquo; or &quot;biodegradable&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; bagged.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;MUST NOT&lt;/strong&gt; be disposed of in the garbage, Blue Bin (recycling) or Green Bin (organics).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take this item to one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311. In an apartment or condo building, pickup needs to be arranged by building staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All invasive plants should be bagged and placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; to prevent spread.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any plastic pieces and place those in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place empty, unsoiled box in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place plastic wrapper and applicator in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any foam that is soiled, shorter than 4&quot; or black in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove plastic overwrap and absorbent pad and place in Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place empty item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt; (recycling). Stained foam is fine, but it must be free of residue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;color: black; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- x-tinymce/html --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This item is &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;MUST NOT&lt;/strong&gt; be disposed of in the garbage, Blue Bin (recycling), Green Bin (organics), drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;color: black; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take this item to any pharmacy, or one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;color: black; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt; or by calling 311. In an apartment/condo, building staff need to request pickup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove plastic handles and place in &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If cardboard is&amp;nbsp;soiled with food, place it in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, break down/flatten unsoiled cardboard and place in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be placed in the Garbage Bin, Blue Bin, Green Bin or put down the drain, toilet or sewer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;It must be brought in any container that has a lid, is securely closed and can be left behind.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If soiled with chemicals such as cleaning products, place in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, this item should be placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt; after removing any batteries and disposing of them as &lt;a href=&quot;Household%20Hazardous Waste&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Roboto, &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Place this item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Roboto, &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Roboto, &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item at the curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you live in a multi-residential building, please take this item to your building&amp;rsquo;s designated area for oversized items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any batteries and dispose of those as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt; (HHW).&amp;nbsp;Place empty container in the garbage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If batteries cannot be removed, then dispose of entire item as HHW.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some retailers/manufacturers may offer product take-back programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is not collected at curbside.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean construction drywall, including painted, papered or vinyl covered, is accepted at certain &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Bermondsey, Commissioners, Ingram).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soak thoroughly in water, then wrap in double plastic bags (to keep them from drying out) before placing in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this cooled item in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If waxed or made of parchment paper, place in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any plastic pieces and place those in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Roboto, &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Place empty, flattened box in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If lined with wax or plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), then place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this empty, unsoiled item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(recycling)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The City does not accept this item in its Blue Bin Recycling or Green Bin Organics programs, even if it is labelled recyclable, compostable or biodegradable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open bag and empty tea into &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place bag in &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If paper is covered with plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this item in an envelope before putting in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt; or add to clear bag with shredded paper.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the paper is the size of a business card or smaller, place in an envelope or add to clear bag of shredded paper before putting in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paper larger than a business card can be placed directly in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNoSpacing&quot;&gt;Place this extinguished and cooled item in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty, unsoiled item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If item is soiled with food, place it in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;, even if empty, and MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin or Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any non-paper components (e.g. mesh) and place those in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty, unsoiled item in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If item is soiled with food, place it in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any non-paper handles and components (e.g. ribbons, rope, grommets) and place those in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If lined with plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), then place in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;Completely submerge fireworks in water and soak them overnight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;Wrap soaked fireworks in a plastic bag (to keep them from drying out) and dispose in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;Dispose of fireworks in small quantities (up to 10 items).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty, rinsed item, with lid on, in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Roboto, &#x27;Helvetica Neue&#x27;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box;&quot;&gt;Remove any batteries and dispose of them as&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #337ab7; text-decoration-line: none;&quot; href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box;&quot;&gt;Place item in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box;&quot;&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If lined with wax or plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), then place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Green Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste (HHW)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and MUST NOT be placed in your Garbage Bin, Blue Bin or Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please take this item to one of the City&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/garbage/depots.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.toronto.ca/environment_days/index.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 to 50 litres/kilograms, residents can also request a free Toxic Taxi pick-up&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/home/311-toronto-at-your-service/create-a-service-request/service-request/?request=0VS6g000000DzdlGAC&quot;&gt;online&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If battery-powered, remove battery and dispose of it as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;mso-list: Ignore;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font: 7.0pt &#x27;Times New Roman&#x27;;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; these items&amp;nbsp;or bringing original (not copies) or unused rewritable ones in cases to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;This item is not collected at the curbside and is not accepted at City of Toronto Drop-Off Depots or Community Environment Days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/long-term-waste-strategy/waste-reduction/?accordion=where-to-donate-items&quot;&gt;Consider donating&lt;/a&gt; reusable items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;Alternatively, please make arrangements with a private company to dispose of this item.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place in a clear plastic bag or in an open cardboard box and set on the ground on Garbage collection day 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin. Residents of apartments/condos should take electronics to their building&amp;rsquo;s designated drop-off area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronics can also be taken to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place plastic and foil wrappers in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paper wrappers are often lined with plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly) and these should also be placed in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the wrapper is entirely paper (i.e. has no lining), place it into an envelope or add to shredded paper and then in the Blue Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any non-paper materials and place those in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place clean paper in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cards with batteries should be disposed of as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/electronic-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Electronic Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If paper is covered with plastic (can be revealed by ripping slowly), place this item in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the paper is the size of a business card or smaller, place in an envelope or add to clear bag of shredded paper before putting in the Blue Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paper larger than a business card can be placed directly in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drain all fuel and dispose of it as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item at your curb on your regular garbage collection day, 0.5 metre (2 feet) away from your Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove any batteries and dispose of them as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place any black plastic and padded cases in the Garbage Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place all other empty plastic cases in the &lt;strong&gt;Blue Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place this empty item in the &lt;strong&gt;Garbage Bin&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This item is &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/household-hazardous-waste/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Household Hazardous Waste&lt;/a&gt; (HHW), even if empty, and MUST NOT be placed in the Garbage Bin, Blue Bin or Green Bin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take this item to one of the City&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/drop-off-depots/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Drop-Off Depots&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.toronto.ca/services-payments/recycling-organics-garbage/community-environment-days/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Community Environment Days&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For HHW between 10 and 50 litres/kilograms, you can request a free Toxic Taxi pickup online or by calling 311.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This type of waste is not accepted by the City of Toronto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do not place this item in the Garbage Bin, Green Bin or Blue Bin, and do not bring this item to the City&#x27;s Drop-Off Depots or Community Environment Days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take to a local police station or make arrangements with a private company specializing in handling this type of waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
